<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870916-0015 </DOCNO><HL> Philadelphia Exchange SetsTrading in Utility Options</HL><DD> 09/16/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> COMMODITY NEWS, FARM PRODUCTS (CMD)STOCK INDEXES (NDX)SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR)SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (SEC) </IN><DATELINE> PHILADELPHIA  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Philadelphia Stock Exchange said it received approval from the Securities and Exchange Commission to trade options on an index of 20 U.S. electric utility stocks.    The index will be weighted according to capitalization of the utilities. Trading is scheduled to begin Tuesday.    Settlement will be &quot;European-style,&quot; the exchange said, meaning that the options can be exercised only at expiration. </TEXT></DOC>